    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can I still attend the auction if you're bidding?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              Absolutely. Many clients prefer to attend and watch. However, it's important you don't
              participate in the bidding. Only the appointed bidder should bid to avoid confusion. Some
              clients prefer not to attend to avoid the stress entirely.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What if the property doesn't sell at auction?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              If the property is passed in (doesn't meet the reserve), we immediately negotiate with
              the selling agent on your behalf. Often the best deals happen post-auction when the
              pressure is on the vendor to sell.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How do you determine the maximum bid?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              We conduct independent market analysis, review comparable sales, and assess the property's
              true value. We then recommend a maximum bid based on this data, which you approve before
              auction day.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Do you guarantee we'll win the auction?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              We can't guarantee you'll win. That depends on other bidders and how much they're willing
              to pay. What we guarantee is strategic bidding that gives you the best chance of success
              at the right price, and the discipline to walk away if bidding exceeds value.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How much does auction representation cost?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              Our auction representation service is a fixed fee of $3,000. This includes pre-auction property analysis, strategic bidding plan, professional representation on auction day, and post-auction negotiation if required. There are no hidden costs or percentage-based fees.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can you bid on properties outside Queensland?</h3>
            <p class="faq-answer">
              Our primary service area is Queensland (<a href="/brisbane-buyers-guide">Brisbane</a>, <a href="/gold-coast-buyers-guide">Gold Coast</a>, Sunshine Coast). If you need
              auction representation outside these areas, contact us to discuss options.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact CTA Section -->
